Rating: 4
Made these crepes gluten-free by substituting gluten-free pancake mix for the flour. The change had absolutely no effect on the results, which were incredibly light, thin, and delicious.

Rating: 3
This is a rich dessert. It made 7 crepes, a goodly amount of sauce and a tiny bit of apples. I'd triple the apple quantity if I were to make it again. Yummy, but a lot of work for the small quantity. I'd make a double or triple recipe as all the parts can be made a few days ahead.

Rating: 4
These are delicious, and were a hit at a dinner party. 2 crepes per person was enough. I didn't have calvados brandy, but plain brandy was good. It was great being able to make crepes and sauce the day before; stirring up the apples just before the party & rewarming at dessert time worked fine. This is a real keeper.

