Rating: 3
I'm a pretty experienced baker but I've always been intimidated by the prospect of making crepes, and now I know why! They are TRICKY. I used up a lot of batter making failed crepes before I figured out the right temperature for my pan, the right amount of batter, how to get them OUT of the darn pan. Jeez louise. BUT the final result was absolutely delicious. I wouldn't recommend making this unless you have Calvados, it really elevates the dish (the main reason I tried). I sauteed my apples in slices rather than chopped, and I added a little caramel sauce, fleur de sel, and creme fraiche right before serving (the creme fraiche was a revelation, really added a wonderful creaminess). The other good thing is that you can assemble everything ahead of time, and just rewarm the filled crepes and drizzle on the sauce right before serving, so it's a good dinner party dessert. That is, if you can handle making the crepes, which I'm not sure I'll have the guts to tackle again very soon.....